A lot of people think if they get a lot of money it’s going to fix all their financial problems and make their life better. 

The truth of the matter about 70 percent of people who win a lottery or receive a large windfall go bankrupt within a few years.

This is why so many people that think cash is king fail miserably. They never learned how to leverage their good credit (OPM)

Why risk your cash to make money when you could use someone else’s.

The worst thing that could happen is your fail and you owe the banks money as well as damage your credit. 

The good thing about credit is it can always be rebuilt, repaired and re-used. Meaning you can always get more 💰

Can you say the same if you spent $112 Million dollars today? How many lifetimes would it take for you to make it all back?

With a contract to purchase a property, you have what's called equitable interest.
